definition.value: A nucleoside analogue having 5-aminomethyl-2-thiouracil as the modified nucleobase.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the exocyclic amino group of 5-aminomethyl-2-thiouridine.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-leucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-histidine residues.
Any capsular polysaccharide derivative which is carried on the surface of a bacterial capsule or formed on the outer portion of a cell wall and masks somatic O antigens.
A member of the class of prostaglandins Falpha that is latanoprost free acid with a double bond at position 13.

An acidic polysaccharide containing N-acetyl-D-glucosamine, N-acetyl-D-mannosaminouronic acid, and 4-acetamido-4,6-dideoxy-D-galactose. A major component of the cell wall outer membrane of Gram-negative bacteria.
A dihydroxyflavanone having the two hydroxy groups located at the C-4' and -7 positions and two additional methoxy substituent at the C-3' and 8-positions.
A glucosaminyl group having D-configuration and an N-acetyl substituent
A carbohydrate acid derivative that is D-mannopyranuronic acid in which the hydroxy group at position 2 is substituted by an acetamido group.

An extended flavonoid that consists of (2S)-flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2', 3', and 6', a 2,4-dihyroxyphenyl group at position 5', a prenyl group at position 8 and a gem-dimethylpyran ring fused across positions 6 and 7.
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of Gly-Pro.
A member of the class of aurones that is aurone with a furan ring fused across positions C-6, and -7.
A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of N-acetyl-D-mannosaminouronic acid
A member of the class of chalcones that is chalcone substituted by methoxy groups at positions 2', 6' and 9 and a dimethylpyrano ring substituted across positions 3' and 4'.
An amino sugar that is 4,6-dideoxy-D-galactose substituted at position 4 by an acetamido group.
A peptide anion that is the conjugate base of Gly-Glu, obtained by deprotonation of the terminal and side-chain carboxy groups and protonation of the terminal amino group.
A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of 4-acetamido-4,6-dideoxy-D-galactose.
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of Ala-Gly.
A flavanone glycoside that is (2S)-flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 4', and a (6''-O-(3,4,5-trihydroxybenzoyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyloxy residue at position 7.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-glutamine residues.

A sulfoxide resulting from the oxidation of the sulfur attached to one of the phenyl groups of GW 501516. It is a urinary metabolite of GW 501516 (a failed drug candidate and gene doping agent whose use by athletes has been prohibited by the World Anti-Doping Agency), so detection of the sulfoxide in sports drugs testing can be used to prove GW 501516 doping.

A sulfone resulting from the oxidation of the sulfur attached to one of the phenyl groups of GW 501516. It is a urinary metabolite of GW 501516 (a failed drug candidate and gene doping agent whose use by athletes has been prohibited by the World Anti-Doping Agency), so detection of the sulfone in sports drugs testing can be used to prove GW 501516 doping.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the 1-O-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.
A phosphatidylcholine 32:1 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are tetradecanoyl and (11Z)-octadec-11-enoyl respectively.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 14:1 in which the remaining acyl group is (9Z)-tetradecenoyl.
A dipeptide formed from glycyl and L-glutamic acid residues.
A C-nitro compound that is cyclohexene substituted at position 1 by a nitro group.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-aspartic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from glycyl and L-aspartic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-isoleucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-methionine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-phenylalanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-tryptophan residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alanyl and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginyl and L-alanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from two L-arginine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginyl and L-aspartic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginyl and L-glutamine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginyl and L-isoleucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginyl and L-leucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginyl and L-leucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginine and L-methionine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginine and L-phenylalanine residues. It exhibits vasorelaxant activity.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginine and L-serine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginine and L-tryptophan residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginine and L-tyrosine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-arginine and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-asparagine and L-glutamic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-asparagine and L-valine residues.
